# Product Requirement Document
**Project:** Personal Professional Landing Page
**Owner:** Drew Peterson
**Course:** BAIS 3300 — Digital Product Management, University of Iowa
**Date:** March 2026

---

## 01 — Problem Statement

Drew Peterson is a dual B.B.A. student in Finance and Business Analytics & Information Systems at the University of Iowa, graduating December 2026. He is targeting Financial Analyst roles at commercial real estate firms in the Midwest.

A PDF resume cannot be found through a Google search. Drew's landing page solves a discoverability problem by creating a permanent, searchable URL tied to his name and professional identity — giving CRE recruiters a live destination to find and evaluate him online. The page complements his resume but does not duplicate it; it serves as a curated professional presence that can be shared during applications and discovered organically.

---

## 02 — Target Audience

**Primary visitors:** Recruiters and hiring managers at commercial real estate firms in the Midwest (e.g., CBRE, JLL, Colliers, regional CRE firms in Chicago, Des Moines, Minneapolis, and Kansas City).

**What they are looking for when they arrive:**
- Evidence of relevant internship experience in finance or real estate-adjacent roles
- Proof of analytical skills through tools and coursework
- Confirmation that Drew is specifically interested in CRE financial analysis, not just finance generally
- Easy access to his LinkedIn and GitHub profiles to evaluate his professional and technical presence

---

## 03 — Goals & Success Metrics

| Goal | How We Measure It |
|------|------------------|
| Page is live and publicly accessible | URL resolves without errors in a browser |
| Page is findable by target employers | URL is shared directly with at least 5 target CRE companies as part of job applications within 30–60 days of launch |
| Page accurately represents Drew's professional identity | All content (bio, skills, contact) is accurate and up to date at launch |

